Talking asleep
Some children talk overnight.
I do not refer to those who are awake and tell us something that happened the day before, but to the children who speak during their sleep.
The first time that happens, it may surprise you, but it doesn’t matter.
It is a benign sleep alteration called sleep sleep.
This is quite common, especially in children and adolescents.
There are more than one talking at night.
This phenomenon can appear very sporadicly (once in life, for example, associated with a high fever episode), or more periodically (every day, once a week, once a month ...), the day after the child is no longer remembered.
There is no single cause that determines its appearance.
They are often linked to other sleep alterations such as nightmares, night terrors, night enurerie (do pipi in bed) or sleeping, but this is not always the case.
As we have already said before, they can also be associated with very heavy fever, stress or overexcitation.
However, this is a little studied phenomenon.
The intensity with which it occurs is also very variable.
He may speak with a little quiet voice, with isolated words, murmurs or, on the contrary, with crying, crying, long speech...
In the event that sleepiness becomes very common, it would be useful to observe the child and consult a specialist, to check whether there is a problem that causes a lot of anxiety and to obtain an explanation for this problem.
We said that it is a benign alteration, so there is no treatment, unless it is related to another alteration in sleep that can be taken care (e.g., if it is related to sleep apnea or stress).
What can be done is to take into account a number of very simple preventive measures such as:
Try not to excite the child before going to sleep.
Therefore, look for quiet games and avoid more or less violent TV programs or shows.
With very nervous children and who are hard to relax, relaxation techniques can be used to help them calm inside.
This will allow the child to have a more peaceful sleep.
As soon as the sleeps appear try to stay calm.
Remember that they are harmless to the child and that the next day he will no longer remember what happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake him up.
It is unnecessary because he is unconscious and you would wake him up.
Even if he speaks, he sleeps and rests.
Remember that if it is very anxious several times, it is advisable to consult a doctor or check what causes so much anxiety in the child.
If you understand what he says (which is not usual), don’t have the temptation to question him for information.
You won’t get anything, because as he sleeps, he is not aware of being able to organize his thought.
Furthermore, you will hear what he says, but you won’t know what he’s dreaming about, then be careful about how you interpret the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Never tell the child that you can ask him at night to know his secrets.
Not even in joking.
This causes a lot of anxiety.
In conclusion, don’t worry, it’s nothing bad, it’s an episode that lasts only a few minutes.
